			<td class="smallfont" align="right">April 5th, 2005 09:10 AM</td>
		</tr>
		</table>
		
		<hr />
		
		
			<div><strong>10-day trial evaluation/complaints/praise</strong><br />&nbsp;</div>
		
		
		
		<div>May have this in the wrong section, but I figure it will get enough traffic.<br />
<br />
Recently went on hiatus in EQ, and a buddy gave me a 10-day free trial of WoW.  It sat around for a bit, but I did eventually give it a shot.<br />
<br />
I''m not trying to start a argument on the relative values of the games, but here is my 2 cents.  I'm posting this so I can get some corrections about gameplay, or a few acknowledgements from palyers that some of the problems have been identified and are being looked at.<br />
<br />
I have tried each race, and each class at least to level 10.  My "main" would be a mage in his 30s.  Blizzard has created a very neat game.  It is fun.  It appears to be something I may play until EQ gets its act together or goes away.  I do prefer EQ in general.  WoW has simplified a number of things which make it a better time killer, though I can't get "attached" to my character as I can in EQ.  I play on a PvP server, <br />
<br />
!, ?:  I like this to a degree.  The quest identifiers are relatively nice.  Its easy to see if you are in a "good" area for your level.  I wish they would be a bit better about making these appear on the mini-map.  That seems hit or miss when looking to complete a quest.  I'd also prefer a different color.<br />
<br />
Griffon Masters:  I think you should be able to "buy" a route without actually traveling there, make it much more expensive the first time, but still available.  It's not like we are training the griffons.  There should be a toggle that makes a griffon master show as a green dot at least on the mini-map if you want it on.  A fast forward option on the griffons would be nice as well.  Translocators please.  Without the Fast forwar you should at least be able to daisy chain routes so I can program the flight from deep elfland to deep humanville and go make dinner, eat dinner, read a book...<br />
<br />
Exploration XP:  Nice, but someone needs to fix the elf areas.  Getting areas to open up in some of those areas is like pulling teeth.  Buyable in-game maps that you can right click to "explore" areas woudl be nice.  Maybe have them show up, but be light grey until you actually get there.<br />
<br />
Groups:  Random people tend to believe its who can push the button faster.  Granted I have not hit 60, but it seems there are alot more "dumb" people playing this game.  I am constantly amazed at the people who throw group invites without saying anything first.  As a side note, if you play a priest, and have no heals hotbuttoned, please tell your party.<br />
<br />
Auction House:  Could do a whole post on this.  Without analyzing the whole she-bang--Overall I prefer the bazaar.<br />
<br />
Level 60:  The level 60 game is strictly for gear enhancement?  This scares me more than any other thing.  No "gear" I have seen yet really jumps out, but I'm not in that range yet.  Are they planning on some form of AA's?<br />
<br />
Quest rewards:  Very irritating getting a quest that rewards you with your choice of 5 items you can't use.  At least post the "sell value" of the items so we can get the most cash.<br />
<br />
Gear:  Might just be mages, but it appears there are no significant alternatives to a 2 handed staff.  If you are using something else you are walking around just for show.  On that note...  I would have sworn someone said that you dont have to wear a robe.  I dislike robes, but other than a few very minor stints I have been forced to wear robes.  I hope at the high end, I am not stuck wearing nothing but robes.  Though, I know I am.  Hats.  Man them are some ugly hats.  I thought EQ clashed bad, but man.  However, If you get matching items in this, it does work much better.  Can you "dye" items in this after they are created or if you receive them as a reward?<br />
<br />
Appearance:  Man, I wish you could change your appeaance after you get in the game.  Also, human males need a nose job.  I don't know who animated the shading on human noses, but you are fired.<br />
<br />
Elves:  No real elves sucks ass.<br />
<br />
Downtime/Lag:  Good lord, 2 day patches.  Lag out the ass, and I'm on a low population server (if those ratings can be believed)  Ironforge is a pain in the arse walking through.  Whoever put the pits near the bank/AH needs to get fired too.<br />
<br />
Tradeskills:  Overall I like these, though I'm not sure why some are considered seperate.  Alchemy/hebalism, Skinning/Leatherworking, Mining/Smithing.  I have no issues with seperate skill numbers, but seems foolish to take one without the other.<br />
Questions here...<br />
Is tinkering practically self-only?  IE its mostly for building stuff for yourself?<br />
Is it intended that other people can skin your kills but herbs/mines are strictly first come/first serve?<br />
Ive noticed that smithing sometimes requires leatherworking products?  many others like that?  havent seen that in alchemy, other than maybe fishing.<br />
<br />
Have they talked about any expansions yet?<br />
<br />
I REALLY don't like that dwarves/gnomes &amp; orcs/trolls share the same starting area.<br />
<br />
Do they have any type of <b><i>in game </i></b> rational for the lack of alliance/horde communication or is this the man behind the curtain we dont ask about?<br />
<br />
Overall, Like I said, good game.  Don't get bent out of shape on those complaints, lots of good things, but I don't need feedback on the good things.<br />
<br />
Last thing said:  The 10 day pass is an incredible idea.  I would never have played without it.  I'll probably become a customer at least for a few months too.</div>
	</td>
</tr>
</table>
