		<hr />
		
		
		
		
		<div>I only want quest turn-ins to show on the mini-map. That'd be enough for me.<br />
There should be quests tucked away in corners of the content for the explorers.  Like the feller atop the mountain in dun murogh.  Full-on quest radar would kill that.<br />
<br />
I like the idea of buyable maps to uncover parts of your overland map, in lieu of getting exploration experience.  I also agree with the desire to allow people to buy 'stringed' fligh paths.  Take me from Aerie Peak to BB please, I'm gonna go make a sandwich.<br />
Speeding up travel itself, I am against.<br />
<br />
Changing hairstyles and dye-ing I agree with, but wouldn't prioritize very high at all.<br />
<br />
Engineering: very much self-only.  Probably the most fun tradeskill though.<br />
Most tradeskills do have quite a bit of interreliance for items (for the stuff you <i>want</i> to make anyway).<br />
<br />
Gnomes/Trolls ... meh. It beats only having 6 player races, and the lore doesn't support much else.  Sometimes I wonder if they weren't meant to be first expansion player races, but got pushed up.<br />
<br />
As for AAs... I'd rather have my talent points from 10-60 than get em all at the end, thanks.<br />
<br />
No cross-faction communication... I prefer it.  I'm much happier with the more Dark Age-ish view of factions than the EQ-ish lack of factions.  Certainly artificial, but it beats the alternative, imo.</div>
	</td>
</tr>
