		<hr />
		
		
		
		
		<div>Note on the Engineering:  Yes, most of it requires engineering to use, several quests use it - For example a Horde Quest wants a Deadly Blunderbus - THere's an Alliance(possibly Horde too) that wants 8 High-Explosive Bombs + 8 Unstable Triggers..  <br />
Most of the Engineering stuff is Tradeable - but not useable unless you have engineering (there are a few exceptions to this)- There are two paths to Engineering Goblin, and Gnome - Gnome makes the most Gadgets, Goblin makes more and bigger and better Bombs - with a few gadgets.  With Most being tradeable, while you may not be able to make a certain Item, You can trade for it from an Engineer of the Opposite discipline.</div>
	</td>
</tr>
