		<hr />
		
		
		
		
		<div>I agree completely on exporing the night elf zones, I hated ashenvale because the discovery areas were so odd in there.  Most other zones I have been to might have 1 weird area, but that whole zone is weird.<br />
<br />
Regarding the level 60 game, soon (whatever that means) battlegrounds and the pvp honor system will be in and that will be something else to do.  Looking further down the road, hero classes will be added, but I think that won't be for awhile, but it will be a way to advance your character at 60.  Right now, there is pvp for fun, pve raiding, loot, quests, faction, etc. at 60.<br />
<br />
For quest rewards, most are pretty good about having at least one thing you can use, but yeah, a few need to add some stuff.  Not a huge deal, but something I would like to see them update and have new quests be good about.<br />
<br />
For 2h staves for casters, typically they are better, but there are some exceptions.  There are always a few daggers, maces, and swords that were built with casters in mind and plenty of decent offhand items for casters.<br />
<br />
Downtime and lag over my whole playing time have not been excessive and they have been generous at adding free days when servers are down for an extended period of time.  Definitely a problem, but it has been improving at least on my server and they are still working on it.<br />
<br />
For tradeskills, I can see what you mean, but the nice thing about them being seperated is that you can choose to just be a gatherer and sell on the AH, just be a producer/user or pick skills that compliment each other.  <br />
<br />
No word about expansions yet, but they have free content updates planned.  No timetable on things, but they are working on battlegrounds and pvp honor and always on more high end pve raid content and instances.<br />
<br />
While it would have given us more world to explore with each race having a unique starting area, it at least is explained from a lore perspective why things are the way they are.<br />
<br />
No in game rational for not being able to communicate with the opposite faction.  It is one of those where enforcing an illogical game mechanic makes the game work the way they want it to.  Part of it is keeping people from insulting, taunting. etc. more than with the standard emotes.  There are plenty of people who disagree on this point, but they are pretty adamant about keeping the factions seperate as far as helping each other out, they want the tension to be there whenever you see an opposite faction member.<br />
<br />
I hope you continue to enjoy the game :)</div>
	</td>
</tr>
</table>
