		<hr />
		
		
		
		
		<div>Quests on the map: Most quests are clustered at the center of population for the zone. The rest represent `discovery' quests. Seems fine to me, and there's enough quests that if you miss one it's not really a character crisis.<br />
<br />
Buy Griffon Routes: No, I like the exploration element. The travel links are short and fast enough that it can give the world a scale without being boring like EQ's 40 minute boats and 15 minute spires. Certainly PoP books, convenient as they were, destroyed any sense of "world" in EQ.<br />
<br />
Exploration XP: The problem with this is they tied map regions to landmarks. Thus you can ride through a non-mapped area and not get it mapped. Of course this tells you that you haven't fully explored the area, which has some benefits.<br />
<br />
Groups:  Pickup groups are a crapshoot, especially in a new game with a huge userbase. No news here.<br />
<br />
Auction House: Don't do drugs.<br />
<br />
Level 60:  No. The level 60 game is meant to have PvE advancement through gear, PvP advancement through status and gear and character progression through hero quests. It's just that most isn't in the game and Blizzard are damn slow about adding. On the positive side much of the high level content is of a very high quality.<br />
<br />
Gear:  Dye sucks. Color is a clue to recognising the identity of the armor.<br />
<br />
Appearance:  Who cares? WoW is meant to be played at medium view distance. How often do you really get close enough to stare into another characters eyes and note the cleft of their chin?<br />
<br />
Elves:  "real" elves?<br />
<br />
Downtime/Lag:  Yeah, Blizzard have issues.<br />
<br />
Alchemy is basically a primary producer itself. All the potions are tradeable and our highest end abilities are largely about supporting other trades. Largely transmuting components for smithing.<br />
<br />
Cross faction comm: Lack of communication works to clearly split the factions which is a good setup for PvP (without trashtalk). I'm not a great fan on how it reduces PvE opportunities. Especially if you're horde with an anemic population.<br />
<br />
Really WoW has lots of issues at the moment and there's lots that could be done better. It will be very interesting to see how it grows. However even in its current stage I think it's the best PvE MMORPG out there at the moment.</div>
	</td>
</tr>
</table>
