		<div>I've never had a problem with the quest identifiers on the mini-map.  There are occassional graphical glitches where the minimap doesn't refresh fast enough.  Perhaps that is what you are seeing.<br />
<br />
Personally, even though it is a pain, I say keep the griffons and don't allow daisy-chaining.  And no translocators.  One of the things that makes WoW special is the fact that the world feels big.  Griffons go a long way towards helping to acheive that.  I only wish boats were actual boat rides, with areas to explore in the middle of the ocean ala OOT.<br />
<br />
I would love to see in-game purchasable maps.  Actually what I really want to see is the ability to make your own custom maps in game and the ability to sell them at the auction house.<br />
<br />
Generally, I wouldn't say there are more stupid people in WoW as much as just that there are less people with experience at mmorpgs.  Probably one out of three have never played another mmorpg in their life.  This means their learning curve is different.<br />
<br />
AH.  Not much to say since you didn't get very specific.  It needs a better search function, and the interface is a bit wierd and redundant.<br />
<br />
The idea of providing monetary value for quest rewards is a good one.  I wish they would just make items you can't use droppable so you can sell them in the AH.<br />
<br />
I dont' have a problem with the graphics in WoW.  They remind me of the old days in EQ, in a very good way.<br />
<br />
The poor choice in models is somewhat tiresome.  But the variety in armor looks makes up for it to a great degree.<br />
<br />
Lag, yeah.</div>
	</td>
