		<hr />
		
		
		
		
		<div>Just to but in on the 2h vs 1h+offhand side argument:<br />
From 46 to 60 I've carried this combination: <a href="http://www.thottbot.com/?i=19595" target="_blank">Inventor's Focal Sword</a> and <a href="http://www.thottbot.com/?i=19570" target="_blank">Cloud Stone</a>.<br />
Combined stats:<br />
Int: 16<br />
Sta: 0<br />
Spi: 10<br />
Arcane Resist: 10<br />
Spell Crits +1%.<br />
<br />
Mind that I got this at 48, off a single (lucky me) Maraudon run. What upgrades this in the 2h category? <a href="http://www.thottbot.com/?i=5291" target="_blank">Trindlehaven Staff</a> off the boss of LBRS (5-manned at the bare minimum), <a href="http://www.thottbot.com/?i=35933" target="_blank">Rod of the Ogre Magi</a> "off" the boss of Dire Maul (5-manned, and not particularly hard to get, but required 58 means it's not an upgrade to the inventor's for a long time), and <a href="http://www.thottbot.com/?i=19726" target="_blank">Staff of Hale Magefire</a> apparently a world drop off 59+ mobs. And epic upgrade would be <a href="http://www.thottbot.com/?i=5621" target="_blank">Glowing Brightwood Staff</a>, but good luck (granted, it's 300-600 gold at the AH occasionally) on that. Of these the only ones I'd actually switch for would be the Rod of the Ogre Magi and Glowing Brightwood. <br />
<br />
Sword and offhand combinations are not useless, there are just less big numbers on 'em. Just about every other horde caster who's done SM a sufficient number of times and hasn't massively outleveled (not that I haven't seen 60s running around with these, /sigh) them is wielding a hypnotic blade and a prophetic cane. The "best" combination/stave varies often, and your own evaluation of stats counts for far more than the official "best." WoW lets you make a lot of choices gear wise, as in the talent system. While everyone's more or less the same in absoute power, the customisation of a character does show up in subtle differences and <i>will</i> result in different strengths and weaknesses. Specialise your character in a manner that conforms to your playstyle, not the other way around, and most of the gear headaches go away.</div>
	</td>
</tr>
</table>
